  "texts": [
    "The average accuracy rises to 92.7% for the tools, 94.8% for the strategies and 94.0% globally, with a standard deviation of 0.029, 0.043 and 0.039 respectively.",
    "The minimum accuracy achieved is now 0.855.",
    "The average F1-score also rises to 0.955 and 0.968 for tools and strategies, respectively, and to 0.966 globally, giving a further proof of the goodness of the implemented classification model.",
    "It is worth noting that, even choosing the best performing ML algorithm with its best setup among all the tested ones, the achieved performance is considerably lower than by choosing a different algorithm for the prediction of each tool and strategy.",
    "In particular, SVM with numeric input and RBF kernel, which reached the highest average weighted accuracy (86.5% and 89.4%, by considering and discarding the performances under 85% accuracy, respectively), showed a performance around 4% lower than the implemented method."
  ],
